  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently when we test our helm charts we get a Success or Fail. \r\n\r\n# Proposed solution\r\nI propose to provide a flag that will allow the users to see the log of the test pod to get information about why it failed or passed\r\n\r\n# Behavior \r\nIn the `helm test <command>`  adding a flag`--log` or `--output` flag. In which, at the end of the test we output the test-pod log if flag is present. If the test pod is still present in the cluster(user did not use the clean up flag), the user should be able to get the output of the test-pod.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
